Day 29 - ROM (Read Only Memory)


In this project, I implemented a simple **8x8 ROM** in Verilog.  
ROM is used to store **constant values** like lookup tables, instruction sets, or sine wave samples.

- **Depth**: 8 locations  
- **Width**: 8 bits  
- **Operation**: Read-only (values preloaded at initialization)  

